questiontext.text:
What is the following number?

Seven hundred and one billion, nine million, six hundred and twenty-five thousand, one hundred and eighteen
A square hall has a perimeter of 32m. What is its area?
The smallest number is:
What is the value of (5 + 3)2 + (5 - 3)2?
Use the Venn diagram to decide how many students love apples if each black dot represents one student.
If a 50 litre drum of petrol is 4/10 full how much petrol does the drum contain?
A meal at a restaurant cost $75.00. If the customer gives a 10% tip, how much did the customer pay in total?

While making soup Kye used 1/3 of a teaspoon of salt and 1/4 of a teaspoon of pepper. 

How much more salt did Kye use?

A rectangle has a length of 8.5 cm and a width of 3 cm. 

The area of the rectangle equals:
What angle is represented by x in the diagram?

Evaluate the expression below for a = 5 and b = -12.

5a - b

Which of the following numbers cannot be divided by 11?

11, 21, 33, 41, 55, 110, 122

A small submarine started its dive at sea level and descended 9.5 metres per minute. 

Which integer represents the submarine’s vertical position after 12 minutes?

A class kept track of how many bottles each student collected for their recycling project. 

How many bottles did Amir and Cai collect all together?
